promises.quoteExact: We will cut taxes, bring manufacturing back to America, and achieve energy independence.

promises.quoteExact: Launch largest mass deportation program in history
promises.summary: Terminate all open borders policies and begin the largest domestic deportation operation in American history, using the National Guard and empowering domestic police forces.

promises.quoteExact: Implement 10-20% tariffs on all foreign goods
promises.summary: Impose tariffs of 10% to 20% on all foreign goods to protect American manufacturing and workers, with potentially higher percentages on specific countries.

promises.quoteExact: End Department of Education
promises.summary: Abolish the federal Department of Education and return control of education policy to states and local communities.

promises.quoteExact: Increase domestic energy production
promises.summary: Dramatically increase American energy production by ending delays in federal drilling permits and leases, with the goal of reducing energy prices.

promises.quoteExact: End all diversity, equity and inclusion programs
promises.summary: Eliminate DEI programs in government institutions and use federal funding as leverage to end DEI initiatives in private sector organizations.

promises.quoteExact: Provide major tax cuts across all income levels
promises.summary: Implement comprehensive tax cuts for middle-class, upper-class, lower-class, and business taxpayers.

promises.quoteExact: End electric vehicle mandates and incentives
promises.summary: Terminate all Biden administration incentives designed to encourage electric vehicle market development while not opposing EVs themselves.

promises.quoteExact: Pardon January 6 defendants
promises.summary: Review cases and consider pardons for individuals prosecuted in connection with the January 6, 2021 Capitol events.

promises.quoteExact: Implement voter ID requirements nationwide
promises.summary: Establish requirements for voter identification in all federal elections to ensure election integrity.

promises.quoteExact: Reduce federal regulations
promises.summary: Implement sweeping deregulation across federal agencies to reduce burden on businesses and individuals.

promises.quoteExact: Finish border wall construction
promises.summary: Complete construction of the wall along the U.S.-Mexico border to secure the southern border.

promises.quoteExact: Restore school prayer and patriotic education
promises.summary: Promote prayer in schools and implement curriculum emphasizing American patriotism and traditional values.

promises.quoteExact: Implement Schedule F for federal employees
promises.summary: Reclassify tens of thousands of federal workers to make them easier to fire and replace with political appointees.

promises.quoteExact: Ban transgender athletes from women's sports
promises.summary: Prohibit biological males from competing in women's sports at all levels where federal funding is involved.

promises.quoteExact: Strengthen NATO but demand fair burden-sharing
promises.summary: Push NATO allies to meet and exceed their 2% GDP defense spending commitments while maintaining American leadership in the alliance.

promises.quoteExact: End birthright citizenship
promises.summary: Issue executive order to end automatic citizenship for children born in the U.S. to parents who are in the country illegally.

promises.quoteExact: Expand school choice and voucher programs
promises.summary: Promote school choice by expanding voucher programs and charter schools across America.

promises.quoteExact: Reduce crime in major cities
promises.summary: Deploy federal law enforcement resources to reduce crime in Democratic-led cities with high crime rates.

promises.quoteExact: Cancel the federal carbon tax
promises.summary: Eliminate the federal carbon tax to make Canada more affordable for families and businesses.

promises.quoteExact: Cut income tax by one percentage point
promises.summary: Reduce the bottom rate of income tax by one percentage point, a 6.6% cut to the amount of tax paid in that bracket, effective by Canada Day.

promises.quoteExact: Eliminate GST for first-time homebuyers
promises.summary: Remove the GST on properties under $1 million for first-time homebuyers to improve housing affordability.

promises.quoteExact: Establish free internal trade by Canada Day
promises.summary: Eliminate inter-provincial trade barriers to create true free trade within Canada, implemented by July 1st.

promises.quoteExact: Boost defense spending to 2% of GDP by 2030
promises.summary: Increase defense spending to meet NATO's 2% GDP target by 2030, with $18 billion allocated over four years for submarines, drones, and icebreakers.

promises.quoteExact: Invest $5 billion in Trade Diversification Corridors
promises.summary: Create the Trade Diversification Corridors Fund with $5 billion to construct critical infrastructure including ports, railroads, terminals, and pipelines.

promises.quoteExact: Diversify Canada's trading partners
promises.summary: Reduce dependence on the United States by establishing new trade relationships and expanding existing ones with countries around the world.

promises.quoteExact: Make Canada a clean energy superpower
promises.summary: Position Canada as a world-leading superpower in both clean and conventional energy through investment, innovation, and industrial competitiveness.

promises.quoteExact: Implement Carbon Border Adjustment Mechanisms
promises.summary: Develop CBAMs as a protective measure for Canada's energy-intensive and trade-exposed sectors to level the playing field internationally.

promises.quoteExact: Temporary cap on immigration levels
promises.summary: Implement a temporary cap on immigration to manage population growth and ensure adequate housing and services.

promises.quoteExact: Invest heavily in housing construction
promises.summary: Significantly increase federal investment in housing to address Canada's housing crisis and improve affordability.

promises.quoteExact: Reign in government spending
promises.summary: Implement fiscal discipline by reducing wasteful government spending while maintaining essential services.

promises.quoteExact: Strengthen Canada-US relationship on defense
promises.summary: Work closely with the United States on continental defense and security while maintaining Canadian sovereignty.

promises.quoteExact: Support clean technology innovation
promises.summary: Drive clean economy growth through investment in innovation and competitive positioning of Canadian clean tech companies.

promises.quoteExact: Create good-paying jobs in clean energy sector
promises.summary: Generate employment opportunities in the clean energy sector while ensuring fair wages and worker protections.

promises.quoteExact: Expand access to childcare
promises.summary: Continue and expand the national childcare program to support working families and ensure affordable, accessible childcare.

promises.quoteExact: Modernize Canada's critical infrastructure
promises.summary: Invest in modernizing aging infrastructure including roads, bridges, water systems, and public transit.

promiseIndustryImpacts.rationale: Infrastructure improvements increase property values and development opportunities
Infrastructure projects require manufactured materials and equipment
Emissions reduction targets impact traditional energy sectors
Climate goals drive investment in clean technology

Expanding healthcare capacity with new beds and nursing staff represents major healthcare sector investment. Hospitals, medical equipment suppliers, pharmaceutical companies, and healthcare staffing firms benefit from capacity expansion.

Building 1.5 million homes by 2031 represents massive residential development program. Ontario real estate sector sees sustained construction activity, though increased supply may moderate price growth in overheated markets.

Large-scale residential construction drives sustained demand for building materials, appliances, and construction equipment. Manufacturers of lumber, drywall, windows, HVAC, and home fixtures benefit from multi-year development pipeline.
Major transit expansion directly benefits transportation sector
Transit expansion increases property values near stations

Building 500,000 homes annually represents massive real estate development opportunity. Increased housing supply drives construction activity, though may moderate price appreciation in overheated markets long-term.

Enhanced border security with troops and barriers requires surveillance technology, physical infrastructure, and security equipment. Defense contractors and border security firms benefit from state-level security spending.

School choice expansion drives demand for educational technology platforms, digital learning tools, and private school management systems. Education technology companies benefit from increased market size and adoption.

Major road and bridge repair initiative drives demand for construction materials, heavy equipment, and infrastructure products. Michigan's manufacturing sector benefits from improved transportation infrastructure reducing logistics costs.
Reduced crime improves retail business environment
Safer neighborhoods increase property values

Tariffs protect domestic manufacturing from foreign competition. Industries with strong domestic production see benefits from reduced import competition, though input cost increases partially offset gains.

Higher import costs squeeze retail profit margins. Retailers face increased costs for imported goods, leading to higher consumer prices and potential demand reduction. Supply chain disruptions add further pressure.

Technology sector relies heavily on global supply chains, particularly for semiconductors and components from China. Tariffs increase manufacturing costs and disrupt established supply networks, pressuring margins.

Retaliatory tariffs from trading partners severely impact agricultural exports. Historical data shows significant declines in farm exports, reduced market access, and supply chain shifts away from US producers.

Tax cuts drive increased capital flows and market activity. Lower capital gains taxes and corporate rates boost investment activity, trading volumes, and financial services demand. Market-friendly policy environment supports sector growth.

Increased disposable income from tax cuts supports real estate demand. Higher earners retaining more after-tax income drives purchases. REITs benefit from favorable tax treatment and increased investment capital.
Tax cuts boost consumer spending power, particularly for higher-income households. Increased disposable income supports retail sales, though benefits skew toward luxury and discretionary categories.
100% bonus depreciation and R&D expensing incentivize capital investment. Lower corporate rates and QBI deduction support business expansion, particularly benefiting capital-intensive manufacturers.
R&D expensing and capital investment incentives strongly favor technology sector. Tax cuts support innovation spending, expansion, and hiring in R&D-driven industries.

Expanded drilling permits, ANWR access, and LNG export approvals significantly boost oil and gas production. Energy emergency declaration fast-tracks infrastructure. Traditional energy sector sees strong job growth and production increases.
Lower energy costs from increased domestic production reduce manufacturing input costs, improving competitiveness and margins for energy-intensive industries.

Reduced clean energy investment and policy support pressures renewable technology sector. Wind project moratorium and reduced federal clean energy funding slow innovation and market growth for clean tech companies.
Reduced regulatory compliance costs improve financial sector profitability. Eased restrictions on capital requirements and trading activities support expanded business operations and risk-taking.
Streamlined permitting and reduced environmental regulations lower barriers to energy production. Faster approval processes for drilling and infrastructure projects accelerate development timelines.
Lower regulatory compliance burdens reduce operating costs. Simplified environmental and labor regulations decrease administrative overhead and increase operational flexibility.

Healthcare deregulation impacts vary by specific measures. Some providers benefit from reduced administrative requirements, but uncertainty around specific regulatory changes limits confidence in projections.

Mass deportations create severe labor shortages in agriculture sector heavily dependent on migrant workers. Reduced workforce availability increases labor costs and threatens crop production capacity.
Deportation operations reduce available labor pool, particularly in construction and food processing. Higher labor costs and recruitment challenges pressure margins and production capacity.
Border security operations require expanded infrastructure, surveillance technology, and equipment. Defense contractors benefit from increased spending on border technology and physical barriers.
Border wall completion requires significant construction materials, technology, and monitoring systems. Defense and construction contractors benefit from multi-billion dollar infrastructure spending.
Elimination of EV subsidies slows electric vehicle adoption, supporting continued demand for traditional fuels. Oil and gas companies benefit from extended gasoline and diesel market dominance.

Removal of federal EV tax credits severely impacts electric vehicle manufacturers and battery technology companies. Reduced consumer adoption rates slow market growth and pressure valuations of EV-focused firms.

Auto manufacturing faces mixed impacts. Traditional vehicle production benefits from continued combustion engine demand, while EV and battery plant investments face uncertainty and potential slowdowns.

Manufacturing revival focus combines tariff protection, tax incentives, and deregulation. Policies aim to reshore production and boost domestic manufacturing competitiveness through multiple supporting mechanisms.

Broader economic growth agenda supports financial sector through increased business activity, capital flows, and market optimism. Pro-business stance encourages investment and financial services demand.
Comprehensive border wall and deportation program severely restricts agricultural labor supply. Industry heavily dependent on migrant workers faces acute labor shortages and rising wage costs.

Largest domestic deportation operation in history requires extensive security infrastructure, surveillance technology, detention facilities, and transportation. Defense contractors and security firms benefit from expanded government spending.
